            <section class="basics">
                <h2>The Basics</h2>
                <p> Exercise is for <strong>everyone</strong>! It can be adapted to anyones needs and it is a vital aspect of living a long and healthy life. Exercise doesn't need to be complicated and for most people it's not about being jacked, or being able to run a marathon, it's about being a better you. Exercise is a lifestyle choice that should be made for the pursuit of self-improvement and it doesn't have to take hours everyday. It is recommended to get around 180 minutes of moderate aerobic activity per week. That's less than 30 minutes a day and an effective resistance training program could take as little 45 minutes, twice a week. You don't have to spend hours killing yourself in a gym to be healthier. So make the choice to be your best self!      
                </p>
